category.name: community/environment
description:
What future do you want?

The way we picture the future plays a big part in everything we do and think. Elon Musk, Sergei Brin, Mark Zuckerberg and other Silicon Valley tech entrepreneurs are currently building the future they want with self-driving cars, asteroid mining, Tesla cars, Google glass etc, inspired by thinkers like Ray Kurzweil and Peter Diamandis.

At the same time, the leaders of the Chinese government are working hard on the future they want, and send Chinese organisations to buy land in faraway countries to safeguard energy and food supplies for the 1.4 billion inhabitants at home.

There is also a growing global grass roots movements based on environmental sustainability with people who are very clear about what future they want. A clean energy future where consumerism is replaced by community and our fixation with growth on a finite planet is questioned. 

Elsewhere, at the edges of the global society, communities such as the Peer-to-peer movement, the Tibetan Buddhists and Al Qaeda are busy building the future that they want. These are communities with few people and radical ideas, but with potential to disrupt large corporations and nation states. 

This Meetup group are for those who like to explore these very different possible futures. We aim to invite people from different fields to try to make sense of trends, shifts in society and the deeper stories that lie beneath.

We will also discuss what we can do to co-create the future that we want. Because the future is not a destination. It is something we create ourselves by what we do (and don't do) in every moment.

We hope to see you soon!
name: Stockholm Futurists
organizer.name: Johan Paulsson

description: The Venus Project proposes an alternative vision of what the future can be if we apply what we already know in order to achieve a sustainable new world civilization. It calls for a straightforward redesign of our culture in which the age-old inadequacies of war, poverty, hunger, debt and unnecessary human suffering are viewed not only as avoidable, but as totally unacceptable. Anything less will result in a continuation of the same catalogue of problems inherent in today's world.

description:
I have been away from Stockholm for 3 years traveling, being homeless :)

I will resume my weekly joy of feeding the homeless in Stockholm centrum area. But  now I do it Saturdays at 12 noon meeting at same place. (Sergels torget) Looking forward to meeting kind hearts.

I bring a pot of homemade soup (simple carrot, potatoe, and barley) in a pressure cooker (seals top so no spills)  in a two wheeled cart (Dramaten-vagn) and dispense in cups on location where they sit. What service!

Are they grateful? Don't expect it but we dont do it for them only but for a higher purpose. (Thats also a story)

Just in case you think doing this doesn't pay, I have a story for those who come to join me. Fact is it does pay but not from me. "What goes around comes around." You get repayed for your love in action in very tangible ways.
name: Stockholmers who like to do good deeds for others

description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Sustainability Meetup! This is a group for all the people interested in living a sustainable life, respecting the nature and the environment we live in. We want to promote ideas such as:

• eating locally and biologically produced food

•  recycling and repairing instead of buying new things

• sharing before possessing

• growing food while preserving biodiversity and soil fertility (for example with permaculture)

• alternative societies, such as Transition Towns

• and all the nice ideas you and us can promote!

We plan to discuss about alternative ways of thinking our way of living, creating a sense of community that our globalised, fast and often alienating society has long forgotten.

description:
Fair Chance is about supporting children growing under challenging conditions which may hinder them from reaching their full potential and achieving their goals.

Such conditions maybe growing up with parents who are absent or disabled, for example due to drug or alcohol abuse, severe medical conditions (physical or mental), or social deprivation like unemployment, immigration, etc.

There are clear scientific evidence that these children are at significant risk to drop off school, start abusing drugs, come into criminality.

But there are also strong evidence that programs like Fair Chance can prevent this. There are components known to support children growing in alienation like programs promoting mental, social, physical development, supporting children natural curiosity and thirst for knowledge and desire to invent and create.

That is what this meetup is about. We will implement those programs IRL! 

Join us and make a difference!
name: Fair Chance

description:
NetSquared gathers together nonprofits and activists, tech leaders and funders, and everyone who's interested in using technology for social change.

NONPROFIT STAFF will find a friendly, welcoming atmosphere for those who aren't experienced with technology, and many chances to ask questions of tech-experienced nonprofits and experts.

TECHNOLOGISTS AND CONSULTANTS will find opportunities to put your expertise to social good, as well as the potential for lasting relationships (be they paid or volunteer) with leading organizations in your community.

ACTIVISTS AND COMMUNITY LEADERS will see and be given the opportunity to present on successful uses of technology for social change. Not content to simply focus on "shiny tech," we'll explore what the true potential for social change is in each case, where community organizing work can be made more effective, and where it will have to push technology forward.

Learn more about NetSquared and find your closest group at http://www.NetSquared.org
name: Tech4Good Stockholm

category.name: community/environment
description:
Do you work in the non-profit world and have questions about the new EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)? Are you wondering what GDPR means for your organisation and what needs to be done to be compliant? Would you like to meet others with similar concerns and muddle through GDPR together? Or are you passionate and knowledgeable about the topic and want to share your knowledge with others? Most importantly...do you like coffee?

Then this meet up is for you!

We are a small group of people working in the non-profit sector who are researching GDPR and want to create a meet up where, at grass roots level, we can share, discuss and put together ideas on how to prepare for this new regulation. All are welcome to the GDPR coffee meet ups! The meetings will be run entirely by the participants and every meeting will begin by collecting topic suggestions from the participants for the first few minutes. Then we will vote and start the discussions in priority order. Confirm your presence and share this event with colleagues and friends!
name: GDPR for Non-Profits

description:
I am Media and Communication Master's student at Stockholm University. Right now I am doing my final thesis which aim is to find out how people from different cultural backgrounds are interpreting news photographs of Syrian children. Previous studies have focused to study who “Western” audience interpret images of "distant other", but I am interested to find out compare if people from “distant” place see these images differently than someone, who is far away from the crisis. I am looking for volunteers, age 20-30, to participate in four focus groups:
1. Syrian women
2. Syrian men
3. Swedish/Nordic women
4. Swedish/Nordic men
The interviews will be conducted during weeks 12 and 13 in Stockholm Free snacks will be offered, and I can also help with travel expenses. Ps. Participants will remain anonymous in the final research paper: the individual’s responses or results cannot be linked to their identity.
name: Volunteers for focus group interview

description:
As many of you know the world population is growing and the future has some serious problems going on, some is just around the corner and some are in your face... The coming food crisis is one of those "problems".

(as why you probably here)

After attending a aquaponic conference, in London, I realised how young this industry is. In Europe we only have a handfull of people running an aquaponic business but at the same time a lot of people is interested in the idea of growing your own food. On my way back home, this idea struck me "Why not create a MeetUp, so the people who is interested can meet each other?!". My hope with this group is to create a place were you can bounce your Urban Farming ideas(with an special direction towards aquaponics) with other people and then learn from each others mistakes. This group will be for discussion, conversation and for networking. And if you, like me, have this "thing" in your stomach that tells you that something is wrong, then I'll see you soon.

category.name: community/environment
description:
The Copenhagen International Volunteer Club (CIVC) was founded in 2011 in order to bring together people of diverse backgrounds and experiences to work on issues of common interest. This group is for everyone regardless of age, nationality or experience who is interested or involved in community service and voluntary work be it in Denmark or elsewhere.

If you are interested in global issues, charity, volunteering and want to meet with others to learn more and exchange ideas , this is the group for you. No experience is necessary, just an interest in making a positive contribution. We want this meet up group to grow and become a creative and active platform for exchanging ideas and inspiration on how to make a positive change, be it on a local or global scale. And then do it.

We have several work groups that you can join: Refugee Issues, Urban Gardening & Food Systems, Animal Welfare, Medical Exchanges and Sustainable Housing in addition to our Campaigns, Logistics and Documentation group which assists the topic-focused work groups.

Our refugee work is, and has, been taking up most of our time and energy since 2013. We have been scaling back this work in recent months due to a drop in the number of refugees coming to Denmark, but there is still a lot of work to be done in this area. However, this fall the focus is shifting back to some of our other activities in sustainable housing, medical exchanges and work around issues of urban gardening and food systems. 

Sign up for one of our regularly scheduled monthly briefing sessions and find out more about how you can get involved.
name: Copenhagen International Volunteer Club
organizer.name: Andrew Madsen

category.name: community/environment
description:
Thorium MSR is a new way of producing energy. When Thorium is combined with a Moltel Salt Reactor (MSR) we believe it is possible to make energy 10 times more safe than any current energy system out there. And 10 times less expensive and produce 100 times less waste than the current nuclear industry.

Moltel Salt Reactors can be used to burn spent nuclear fuel from the old generations of nuclear power plants, such that the amount of long lived waste is reduced from approx. 100.000 years to 300 years. A molten salt reactor is made from pipes and pumps and valves, thus it should be possible to get the price of energy production via MSR far below any current energy source. In this meetup group we discuss the problems and potentials of the above and what we can do to make it happen.


https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=inIVcUlQZrE
name: Thorium MSR Copenhagen

category.name: community/environment
description:
Cleanweb is a global movement that focuses on tackling big issues with software - leveraging data and ICT to do more with less resource usage.

Example of the Cleanweb: Airbnb, which helps travelers use 66 percent less energy than if they stay in a hotel. ZipCar, which replaces 15 privately owned cars for every shared car on the road. Potential for changing status-quo: HUGE

Are you excited? Are you looking to meet smart people? Expand your network, not only in Denmark but globally? Are you looking for a place to use your skills and expertise to built something that matters?

Our goal is to accelerate the development of new solutions and businesses that utilizes resources more efficiently and more sustainable - Build and share the knowledge and competencies required to build Cleanweb solutions - Establish collaborations across the traditional borders between the different communities, industries and authorities that must be involved to solve the big issues.

Let's start sharing, challenging and building new solutions - CleanwebDK
name: Cleanweb DK

category.name: community/environment
description:
One Bowl is a non-profit, community Restaurant. The community restaurant concept is a restaurant based on a gift economy, allowing people to "pay what you feel" and serving all members of the community regardless of their ability to pay. 

This is based on the values that we would like to treat everyone equal, trustworthy, with dignity without any discrimination. We also want to be socially inclusive, including everyone with their preferences, culture and celebrate diversity. We will serve vegetarian, because we can include more people with Veggies.  We are dependent on your generosity and volunteers to help us work to make our these values possible in our community. 

If your interested in being a volunteer, write to volunteer@onebowl.dk.  You don't have to be particularly skillful, we believe that if you have the passion, one can learn any skill in time.

Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/1bowl

Homepage: https://www.onebowl.dk

description: Welcome to the Copenhagen Maptime chapter, Denmark's first! Maptime was an idea that came to life at the 2013 State of the Map US conference with the underlying premise to get more people involved with OpenStreetMap (OSM). Maptime Copenhagen aims to bring this idea to Denmark and get all kinds of people involved with mapping in a fun, open environment. We will be holding events at exciting locations in Greater Copenhagen using Mapillary and other tools to gather detailed information on the selected area. Whether you are a dedicated OSM contributor with thousands of edits under your belt, a Mapillary champion or brand new to the world of mapping, all are welcome. Stay tuned...more from us soon!

category.name: community/environment
description:
A group for anyone who wants to stay up to date on all events taking place at think.dk! 

PLEASE NOTE: we're also using our homepage and Facebook to promote our events.

think.dk is the Center for Acceleration of Change.

We are a co-creative community, think tank and event platform that supports the development of a sustainable society. An intersection point for Changers of all kind, making room for new ideas. We support people to share knowledge and built the future of their dreams.

We don't mind not fitting in. We are what we have to be to support the change this world needs to see. Nothing's going to change if we just sit and wait.

At think.dk, you can: 

• attend talks and movie screenings on sustainability topics

• join workshops on implementing sustainability in your everyday life 

• learn about open source programming for a more sustainable digital world 

• borrow tools or equipment from think.dk and share your own 

• find body/mind balance in our yoga classes 

• connect with like-minded people 

• use our location for your own sustainability-related event 

• help accelerate sustainable change 

Practically, we are trying to save the world.

Today, there exist numerous initiatives for a more sustainable lifestyle, but they stay hidden in niches because they lack a lobby - and people are stuck in their old habits.

This is why we host a platform for new ideas and offer events and services which further sustainability, sharing, and collaboration. 

We reconnect the dots. Question the box and restore the circle, in order to find real solutions to the problems that (will) affect us all. We experiment. Encourage discussions on new paradigms, explore new work and collaboration patterns and empower people to live more sustainably.

We want to offer serious and sustainable solutions to the problems that affect everyone every day. And we want to make a difference. We are extremely happy to say that the same goes for all of our members. What about you?

It's not about what we could do in the past, but what we can do today. We think that this is how tomorrow is made.

It is time to take the next step. 

Join us now.
name: think.dk - Center for Acceleration of Change

description: We all need to take a break from thinking every once and a while, but we aren’t always so great at taking the time out to do so. We invite you to turn off your cell phone, close your laptop, sit comfortably and simply share a moment of community silence together. Silence allows us to calm our busy minds and with luck (and practice!) to come into contact with our true self without the distractions and input of external stimuli. If you're into grassroot movements, simple living, peace building, integrity, creating community, equality, and need a little more space for spiritual growth then this meetup is perfect for you!!
name: Copenhagen Stillness and Reflection Meetup

description:
This is a group for anyone interested in Coop, sustainability, organic food, local food, animal welfare, volunteering.

Coop Garage is a grassroot project, created by Coop members. Not affiliated with Coop Denmark A/S.

We will arrange talks, meetups, presentations, projects for all interested.

All discussions are fact-based and respectful for opinions.

We meet in Kødbyen, walking distance from Copenhagen Central Station. We are associated with Coop Amba, the largest Coop in Denmark with 1.7 mio members, but are run entirely by volunteers.

description: Welcome to the Copenhagen Maptime chapter, Denmark's first! Maptime was an idea that came to life at the 2013 State of the Map US conference with the underlying premise to get more people involved with OpenStreetMap (OSM). Maptime Copenhagen aims to bring this idea to Denmark and get all kinds of people involved with mapping in a fun, open environment. We will be holding events at exciting locations in Greater Copenhagen using Mapillary and other tools to gather detailed information on the selected area. Whether you are a dedicated OSM contributor with thousands of edits under your belt, a Mapillary champion or brand new to the world of mapping, all are welcome. Stay tuned...more from us soon!

category.name: community/environment
description:
A group for anyone who wants to stay up to date on all events taking place at think.dk! 

PLEASE NOTE: we're also using our homepage and Facebook to promote our events.

think.dk is the Center for Acceleration of Change.

We are a co-creative community, think tank and event platform that supports the development of a sustainable society. An intersection point for Changers of all kind, making room for new ideas. We support people to share knowledge and built the future of their dreams.

We don't mind not fitting in. We are what we have to be to support the change this world needs to see. Nothing's going to change if we just sit and wait.

At think.dk, you can: 

• attend talks and movie screenings on sustainability topics

• join workshops on implementing sustainability in your everyday life 

• learn about open source programming for a more sustainable digital world 

• borrow tools or equipment from think.dk and share your own 

• find body/mind balance in our yoga classes 

• connect with like-minded people 

• use our location for your own sustainability-related event 

• help accelerate sustainable change 

Practically, we are trying to save the world.

Today, there exist numerous initiatives for a more sustainable lifestyle, but they stay hidden in niches because they lack a lobby - and people are stuck in their old habits.

This is why we host a platform for new ideas and offer events and services which further sustainability, sharing, and collaboration. 

We reconnect the dots. Question the box and restore the circle, in order to find real solutions to the problems that (will) affect us all. We experiment. Encourage discussions on new paradigms, explore new work and collaboration patterns and empower people to live more sustainably.

We want to offer serious and sustainable solutions to the problems that affect everyone every day. And we want to make a difference. We are extremely happy to say that the same goes for all of our members. What about you?

It's not about what we could do in the past, but what we can do today. We think that this is how tomorrow is made.

It is time to take the next step. 

Join us now.
name: think.dk - Center for Acceleration of Change

description:
As many of you know the world population is growing and the future has some serious problems going on, some is just around the corner and some are in your face... The coming food crisis is one of those "problems".

(as why you probably here)

After attending a aquaponic conference, in London, I realised how young this industry is. In Europe we only have a handfull of people running an aquaponic business but at the same time a lot of people is interested in the idea of growing your own food. On my way back home, this idea struck me "Why not create a MeetUp, so the people who is interested can meet each other?!". My hope with this group is to create a place were you can bounce your Urban Farming ideas(with an special direction towards aquaponics) with other people and then learn from each others mistakes. This group will be for discussion, conversation and for networking. And if you, like me, have this "thing" in your stomach that tells you that something is wrong, then I'll see you soon.

description:
Vårt syfte är att ha en plats där vi som jobbar (eller vill jobba) praktiskt med omställning kan resonera och byta erfarenheter. 

Tillväxttåget rusar inte längre fram men fortfarande följer det samma gamla spår. Det är svårt att hoppa av mellan stationerna men vi kan förbereda oss. 

Till att börja med kommer vi att fokusera på Tjörnarp. Enligt kommunens förslag till översiktsplan ska byn utvecklas. Översiktsplanen är utställd till den 23 mars för allmänhetens granskning. Märkligt nog jobbar man samtidigt med en besparingsplan där man föreslår att skolan ska läggas ner. 

Höörs kommun följer ett vanligt men simpelt mönster. Trots att alla kommuner vill växa så krymper de flesta och får en försämrad ekonomi. De tvingas spara där det går. Den enkla modellen är att centralisera verksamheterna till centralorten och låta byarna dö. Några tankar på att ställa om med hänsyn till den globala energi- och livsmedelssituationen har man inte. Men det har vi. 

De som vill vara med om att jobba praktiskt med en omställningsplan för Tjörnarp är välkomna att haka på. En omställningsplan för Tjörnarp skulle kunna fogas in i Höörs översiktsplan. Här har vi chansen att utveckla vår egen metod för att utarbeta lokala omställningsplaner.
name: Praktisk omställning
organizer.name: Oscar Kjellberg

category.name: community/environment
description:
What future do you want?

The way we picture the future plays a big part in everything we do and think. Elon Musk, Sergei Brin, Mark Zuckerberg and other Silicon Valley tech entrepreneurs are currently building the future they want with self-driving cars, asteroid mining, Tesla cars, Google glass etc, inspired by thinkers like Ray Kurzweil and Peter Diamandis.

At the same time, the leaders of the Chinese government are working hard on the future they want, and send Chinese organisations to buy land in faraway countries to safeguard energy and food supplies for the 1.4 billion inhabitants at home.

There is also a growing global grass roots movements based on environmental sustainability with people who are very clear about what future they want. A clean energy future where consumerism is replaced by community and our fixation with growth on a finite planet is questioned. 

Elsewhere, at the edges of the global society, communities such as the Peer-to-peer movement, the Tibetan Buddhists and Al Qaeda are busy building the future that they want. These are communities with few people and radical ideas, but with potential to disrupt large corporations and nation states. 

This Meetup group are for those who like to explore these very different possible futures. We aim to invite people from different fields to try to make sense of trends, shifts in society and the deeper stories that lie beneath.

We will also discuss what we can do to co-create the future that we want. Because the future is not a destination. It is something we create ourselves by what we do (and don't do) in every moment.

We hope to see you soon!

description: The Venus Project proposes an alternative vision of what the future can be if we apply what we already know in order to achieve a sustainable new world civilization. Anything less will result in a continuation of the same catalogue of problems inherent in today's world.

category.name: community/environment
description:
I have been away from Stockholm for 3 years traveling, being homeless :)

I will resume my weekly joy of feeding the homeless in Stockholm centrum area. But  now I do it Saturdays at 12 noon meeting at same place. (Sergels torget) Looking forward to meeting kind hearts.

I bring a pot of homemade soup (simple carrot, potatoe, and barley) in a pressure cooker (seals top so no spills)  in a two wheeled cart (Dramaten-vagn) and dispense in cups on location where they sit. What service!

Are they grateful? Don't expect it but we dont do it for them only but for a higher purpose. (Thats also a story)

Just in case you think doing this doesn't pay, I have a story for those who come to join me. Fact is it does pay but not from me. "What goes around comes around." You get repayed for your love in action in very tangible ways.
name: Stockholmers who like to do good deeds for others
organizer.name: daniel behr

description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Sustainability Meetup! This is a group for all the people interested in living a sustainable life, respecting the nature and the environment we live in. We want to promote ideas such as:

• eating locally and biologically produced food

•  recycling and repairing instead of buying new things

• sharing before possessing

• growing food while preserving biodiversity and soil fertility (for example with permaculture)

• alternative societies, such as Transition Towns

• and all the nice ideas you and us can promote!

We plan to discuss about alternative ways of thinking our way of living, creating a sense of community that our globalised, fast and often alienating society has long forgotten.
name: Stockholm Sustainability Meetup

category.name: community/environment
description:
Fair Chance is about supporting children growing under challenging conditions which may hinder them from reaching their full potential and achieving their goals.

Such conditions maybe growing up with parents who are absent or disabled, for example due to drug or alcohol abuse, severe medical conditions (physical or mental), or social deprivation like unemployment, immigration, etc.

There are clear scientific evidence that these children are at significant risk to drop off school, start abusing drugs, come into criminality.

But there are also strong evidence that programs like Fair Chance can prevent this. There are components known to support children growing in alienation like programs promoting mental, social, physical development, supporting children natural curiosity and thirst for knowledge and desire to invent and create.

That is what this meetup is about. We will implement those programs IRL! 

Join us and make a difference!
name: Fair Chance

description:
NetSquared gathers together nonprofits and activists, tech leaders and funders, and everyone who's interested in using technology for social change.

NONPROFIT STAFF will find a friendly, welcoming atmosphere for those who aren't experienced with technology, and many chances to ask questions of tech-experienced nonprofits and experts.

TECHNOLOGISTS AND CONSULTANTS will find opportunities to put your expertise to social good, as well as the potential for lasting relationships (be they paid or volunteer) with leading organizations in your community.

ACTIVISTS AND COMMUNITY LEADERS will see and be given the opportunity to present on successful uses of technology for social change. Not content to simply focus on "shiny tech," we'll explore what the true potential for social change is in each case, where community organizing work can be made more effective, and where it will have to push technology forward.

Learn more about NetSquared and find your closest group at http://www.NetSquared.org
name: Tech4Good Stockholm

category.name: community/environment
description:
Do you work in the non-profit world and have questions about the new EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)? Are you wondering what GDPR means for your organisation and what needs to be done to be compliant? Would you like to meet others with similar concerns and muddle through GDPR together? Or are you passionate and knowledgeable about the topic and want to share your knowledge with others? Most importantly...do you like coffee?

Then this meet up is for you!

We are a small group of people working in the non-profit sector who are researching GDPR and want to create a meet up where, at grass roots level, we can share, discuss and put together ideas on how to prepare for this new regulation. All are welcome to the GDPR coffee meet ups! The meetings will be run entirely by the participants and every meeting will begin by collecting topic suggestions from the participants for the first few minutes. Then we will vote and start the discussions in priority order. Confirm your presence and share this event with colleagues and friends!
name: GDPR for Non-Profits

description:
I am Media and Communication Master's student at Stockholm University. Right now I am doing my final thesis which aim is to find out how people from different cultural backgrounds are interpreting news photographs of Syrian children. Previous studies have focused to study who “Western” audience interpret images of "distant other", but I am interested to find out compare if people from “distant” place see these images differently than someone, who is far away from the crisis. I am looking for volunteers, age 20-30, to participate in four focus groups:
1. Syrian women
2. Syrian men
3. Swedish/Nordic women
4. Swedish/Nordic men
The interviews will be conducted during weeks 12 and 13 in Stockholm Free snacks will be offered, and I can also help with travel expenses. Ps. Participants will remain anonymous in the final research paper: the individual’s responses or results cannot be linked to their identity.
name: Volunteers for focus group interview

description:
As many of you know the world population is growing and the future has some serious problems going on, some is just around the corner and some are in your face... The coming food crisis is one of those "problems".

(as why you probably here)

After attending a aquaponic conference, in London, I realised how young this industry is. In Europe we only have a handfull of people running an aquaponic business but at the same time a lot of people is interested in the idea of growing your own food. On my way back home, this idea struck me "Why not create a MeetUp, so the people who is interested can meet each other?!". My hope with this group is to create a place were you can bounce your Urban Farming ideas(with an special direction towards aquaponics) with other people and then learn from each others mistakes. This group will be for discussion, conversation and for networking. And if you, like me, have this "thing" in your stomach that tells you that something is wrong, then I'll see you soon.
name: Göteborg Aquaponics Meetup (Urban farming)

description:
What future do you want?

The way we picture the future plays a big part in everything we do and think. Elon Musk, Sergei Brin, Mark Zuckerberg and other Silicon Valley tech entrepreneurs are currently building the future they want with self-driving cars, asteroid mining, Tesla cars, Google glass etc, inspired by thinkers like Ray Kurzweil and Peter Diamandis.

At the same time, the leaders of the Chinese government are working hard on the future they want, and send Chinese organisations to buy land in faraway countries to safeguard energy and food supplies for the 1.4 billion inhabitants at home.

There is also a growing global grass roots movements based on environmental sustainability with people who are very clear about what future they want. A clean energy future where consumerism is replaced by community and our fixation with growth on a finite planet is questioned. 

Elsewhere, at the edges of the global society, communities such as the Peer-to-peer movement, the Tibetan Buddhists and Al Qaeda are busy building the future that they want. These are communities with few people and radical ideas, but with potential to disrupt large corporations and nation states. 

This Meetup group are for those who like to explore these very different possible futures. We aim to invite people from different fields to try to make sense of trends, shifts in society and the deeper stories that lie beneath.

We will also discuss what we can do to co-create the future that we want. Because the future is not a destination. It is something we create ourselves by what we do (and don't do) in every moment.

We hope to see you soon!

description:
I have been away from Stockholm for 3 years traveling, being homeless :)

I will resume my weekly joy of feeding the homeless in Stockholm centrum area. But  now I do it Saturdays at 12 noon meeting at same place. (Sergels torget) Looking forward to meeting kind hearts.

I bring a pot of homemade soup (simple carrot, potatoe, and barley) in a pressure cooker (seals top so no spills)  in a two wheeled cart (Dramaten-vagn) and dispense in cups on location where they sit. What service!

Are they grateful? Don't expect it but we dont do it for them only but for a higher purpose. (Thats also a story)

Just in case you think doing this doesn't pay, I have a story for those who come to join me. Fact is it does pay but not from me. "What goes around comes around." You get repayed for your love in action in very tangible ways.
name: Stockholmers who like to do good deeds for others

description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Sustainability Meetup! This is a group for all the people interested in living a sustainable life, respecting the nature and the environment we live in. We want to promote ideas such as:

• eating locally and biologically produced food

•  recycling and repairing instead of buying new things

• sharing before possessing

• growing food while preserving biodiversity and soil fertility (for example with permaculture)

• alternative societies, such as Transition Towns

• and all the nice ideas you and us can promote!

We plan to discuss about alternative ways of thinking our way of living, creating a sense of community that our globalised, fast and often alienating society has long forgotten.

description:
Fair Chance is about supporting children growing under challenging conditions which may hinder them from reaching their full potential and achieving their goals.

Such conditions maybe growing up with parents who are absent or disabled, for example due to drug or alcohol abuse, severe medical conditions (physical or mental), or social deprivation like unemployment, immigration, etc.

There are clear scientific evidence that these children are at significant risk to drop off school, start abusing drugs, come into criminality.

But there are also strong evidence that programs like Fair Chance can prevent this. There are components known to support children growing in alienation like programs promoting mental, social, physical development, supporting children natural curiosity and thirst for knowledge and desire to invent and create.

That is what this meetup is about. We will implement those programs IRL! 

Join us and make a difference!
name: Fair Chance

description:
NetSquared gathers together nonprofits and activists, tech leaders and funders, and everyone who's interested in using technology for social change.

NONPROFIT STAFF will find a friendly, welcoming atmosphere for those who aren't experienced with technology, and many chances to ask questions of tech-experienced nonprofits and experts.

TECHNOLOGISTS AND CONSULTANTS will find opportunities to put your expertise to social good, as well as the potential for lasting relationships (be they paid or volunteer) with leading organizations in your community.

ACTIVISTS AND COMMUNITY LEADERS will see and be given the opportunity to present on successful uses of technology for social change. Not content to simply focus on "shiny tech," we'll explore what the true potential for social change is in each case, where community organizing work can be made more effective, and where it will have to push technology forward.

Learn more about NetSquared and find your closest group at http://www.NetSquared.org

category.name: community/environment
description:
Do you work in the non-profit world and have questions about the new EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)? Are you wondering what GDPR means for your organisation and what needs to be done to be compliant? Would you like to meet others with similar concerns and muddle through GDPR together? Or are you passionate and knowledgeable about the topic and want to share your knowledge with others? Most importantly...do you like coffee?

Then this meet up is for you!

We are a small group of people working in the non-profit sector who are researching GDPR and want to create a meet up where, at grass roots level, we can share, discuss and put together ideas on how to prepare for this new regulation. All are welcome to the GDPR coffee meet ups! The meetings will be run entirely by the participants and every meeting will begin by collecting topic suggestions from the participants for the first few minutes. Then we will vote and start the discussions in priority order. Confirm your presence and share this event with colleagues and friends!
name: GDPR for Non-Profits

category.name: community/environment
description:
I am Media and Communication Master's student at Stockholm University. Right now I am doing my final thesis which aim is to find out how people from different cultural backgrounds are interpreting news photographs of Syrian children. Previous studies have focused to study who “Western” audience interpret images of "distant other", but I am interested to find out compare if people from “distant” place see these images differently than someone, who is far away from the crisis. I am looking for volunteers, age 20-30, to participate in four focus groups:
1. Syrian women
2. Syrian men
3. Swedish/Nordic women
4. Swedish/Nordic men
The interviews will be conducted during weeks 12 and 13 in Stockholm Free snacks will be offered, and I can also help with travel expenses. Ps. Participants will remain anonymous in the final research paper: the individual’s responses or results cannot be linked to their identity.
name: Volunteers for focus group interview

category.name: community/environment
description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Sustainability Meetup! This is a group for all the people interested in living a sustainable life, respecting the nature and the environment we live in. We want to promote ideas such as:

• eating locally and biologically produced food

•  recycling and repairing instead of buying new things

• sharing before possessing

• growing food while preserving biodiversity and soil fertility (for example with permaculture)

• alternative societies, such as Transition Towns

• and all the nice ideas you and us can promote!

We plan to discuss about alternative ways of thinking our way of living, creating a sense of community that our globalised, fast and often alienating society has long forgotten.
name: Stockholm Sustainability Meetup

category.name: community/environment
description:
Fair Chance is about supporting children growing under challenging conditions which may hinder them from reaching their full potential and achieving their goals.

Such conditions maybe growing up with parents who are absent or disabled, for example due to drug or alcohol abuse, severe medical conditions (physical or mental), or social deprivation like unemployment, immigration, etc.

There are clear scientific evidence that these children are at significant risk to drop off school, start abusing drugs, come into criminality.

But there are also strong evidence that programs like Fair Chance can prevent this. There are components known to support children growing in alienation like programs promoting mental, social, physical development, supporting children natural curiosity and thirst for knowledge and desire to invent and create.

That is what this meetup is about. We will implement those programs IRL! 

Join us and make a difference!
name: Fair Chance

description:
NetSquared gathers together nonprofits and activists, tech leaders and funders, and everyone who's interested in using technology for social change.

NONPROFIT STAFF will find a friendly, welcoming atmosphere for those who aren't experienced with technology, and many chances to ask questions of tech-experienced nonprofits and experts.

TECHNOLOGISTS AND CONSULTANTS will find opportunities to put your expertise to social good, as well as the potential for lasting relationships (be they paid or volunteer) with leading organizations in your community.

ACTIVISTS AND COMMUNITY LEADERS will see and be given the opportunity to present on successful uses of technology for social change. Not content to simply focus on "shiny tech," we'll explore what the true potential for social change is in each case, where community organizing work can be made more effective, and where it will have to push technology forward.

Learn more about NetSquared and find your closest group at http://www.NetSquared.org
name: Tech4Good Stockholm

category.name: community/environment
description:
Do you work in the non-profit world and have questions about the new EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)? Are you wondering what GDPR means for your organisation and what needs to be done to be compliant? Would you like to meet others with similar concerns and muddle through GDPR together? Or are you passionate and knowledgeable about the topic and want to share your knowledge with others? Most importantly...do you like coffee?

Then this meet up is for you!

We are a small group of people working in the non-profit sector who are researching GDPR and want to create a meet up where, at grass roots level, we can share, discuss and put together ideas on how to prepare for this new regulation. All are welcome to the GDPR coffee meet ups! The meetings will be run entirely by the participants and every meeting will begin by collecting topic suggestions from the participants for the first few minutes. Then we will vote and start the discussions in priority order. Confirm your presence and share this event with colleagues and friends!
name: GDPR for Non-Profits

description:
I am Media and Communication Master's student at Stockholm University. Right now I am doing my final thesis which aim is to find out how people from different cultural backgrounds are interpreting news photographs of Syrian children. Previous studies have focused to study who “Western” audience interpret images of "distant other", but I am interested to find out compare if people from “distant” place see these images differently than someone, who is far away from the crisis. I am looking for volunteers, age 20-30, to participate in four focus groups:
1. Syrian women
2. Syrian men
3. Swedish/Nordic women
4. Swedish/Nordic men
The interviews will be conducted during weeks 12 and 13 in Stockholm Free snacks will be offered, and I can also help with travel expenses. Ps. Participants will remain anonymous in the final research paper: the individual’s responses or results cannot be linked to their identity.
name: Volunteers for focus group interview

category.name: community/environment
description:
Vårt syfte är att ha en plats där vi som jobbar (eller vill jobba) praktiskt med omställning kan resonera och byta erfarenheter. 

Tillväxttåget rusar inte längre fram men fortfarande följer det samma gamla spår. Det är svårt att hoppa av mellan stationerna men vi kan förbereda oss. 

Till att börja med kommer vi att fokusera på Tjörnarp. Enligt kommunens förslag till översiktsplan ska byn utvecklas. Översiktsplanen är utställd till den 23 mars för allmänhetens granskning. Märkligt nog jobbar man samtidigt med en besparingsplan där man föreslår att skolan ska läggas ner. 

Höörs kommun följer ett vanligt men simpelt mönster. Trots att alla kommuner vill växa så krymper de flesta och får en försämrad ekonomi. De tvingas spara där det går. Den enkla modellen är att centralisera verksamheterna till centralorten och låta byarna dö. Några tankar på att ställa om med hänsyn till den globala energi- och livsmedelssituationen har man inte. Men det har vi. 

De som vill vara med om att jobba praktiskt med en omställningsplan för Tjörnarp är välkomna att haka på. En omställningsplan för Tjörnarp skulle kunna fogas in i Höörs översiktsplan. Här har vi chansen att utveckla vår egen metod för att utarbeta lokala omställningsplaner.
name: Praktisk omställning

category.name: community/environment
description:
What future do you want?

The way we picture the future plays a big part in everything we do and think. Elon Musk, Sergei Brin, Mark Zuckerberg and other Silicon Valley tech entrepreneurs are currently building the future they want with self-driving cars, asteroid mining, Tesla cars, Google glass etc, inspired by thinkers like Ray Kurzweil and Peter Diamandis.

At the same time, the leaders of the Chinese government are working hard on the future they want, and send Chinese organisations to buy land in faraway countries to safeguard energy and food supplies for the 1.4 billion inhabitants at home.

There is also a growing global grass roots movements based on environmental sustainability with people who are very clear about what future they want. A clean energy future where consumerism is replaced by community and our fixation with growth on a finite planet is questioned. 

Elsewhere, at the edges of the global society, communities such as the Peer-to-peer movement, the Tibetan Buddhists and Al Qaeda are busy building the future that they want. These are communities with few people and radical ideas, but with potential to disrupt large corporations and nation states. 

This Meetup group are for those who like to explore these very different possible futures. We aim to invite people from different fields to try to make sense of trends, shifts in society and the deeper stories that lie beneath.

We will also discuss what we can do to co-create the future that we want. Because the future is not a destination. It is something we create ourselves by what we do (and don't do) in every moment.

We hope to see you soon!

description: The Venus Project proposes an alternative vision of what the future can be if we apply what we already know in order to achieve a sustainable new world civilization. It calls for a straightforward redesign of our culture in which the age-old inadequacies of war, poverty, hunger, debt and unnecessary human suffering are viewed not only as avoidable, but as totally unacceptable. Anything less will result in a continuation of the same catalogue of problems inherent in today's world.
name: The Venus project "Designing the future"

description:
I have been away from Stockholm for 3 years traveling, being homeless :)

I will resume my weekly joy of feeding the homeless in Stockholm centrum area. But  now I do it Saturdays at 12 noon meeting at same place. (Sergels torget) Looking forward to meeting kind hearts.

I bring a pot of homemade soup (simple carrot, potatoe, and barley) in a pressure cooker (seals top so no spills)  in a two wheeled cart (Dramaten-vagn) and dispense in cups on location where they sit. What service!

Are they grateful? Don't expect it but we dont do it for them only but for a higher purpose. (Thats also a story)

Just in case you think doing this doesn't pay, I have a story for those who come to join me. Fact is it does pay but not from me. "What goes around comes around." You get repayed for your love in action in very tangible ways.
name: Stockholmers who like to do good deeds for others
organizer.name: daniel behr

description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Sustainability Meetup! This is a group for all the people interested in living a sustainable life, respecting the nature and the environment we live in. We want to promote ideas such as:

• eating locally and biologically produced food

•  recycling and repairing instead of buying new things

• sharing before possessing

• growing food while preserving biodiversity and soil fertility (for example with permaculture)

• alternative societies, such as Transition Towns

• and all the nice ideas you and us can promote!

We plan to discuss about alternative ways of thinking our way of living, creating a sense of community that our globalised, fast and often alienating society has long forgotten.
name: Stockholm Sustainability Meetup

category.name: community/environment
description:
Fair Chance is about supporting children growing under challenging conditions which may hinder them from reaching their full potential and achieving their goals.

Such conditions maybe growing up with parents who are absent or disabled, for example due to drug or alcohol abuse, severe medical conditions (physical or mental), or social deprivation like unemployment, immigration, etc.

There are clear scientific evidence that these children are at significant risk to drop off school, start abusing drugs, come into criminality.

But there are also strong evidence that programs like Fair Chance can prevent this. There are components known to support children growing in alienation like programs promoting mental, social, physical development, supporting children natural curiosity and thirst for knowledge and desire to invent and create.

That is what this meetup is about. We will implement those programs IRL! 

Join us and make a difference!
name: Fair Chance

category.name: community/environment
description:
NetSquared gathers together nonprofits and activists, tech leaders and funders, and everyone who's interested in using technology for social change.

NONPROFIT STAFF will find a friendly, welcoming atmosphere for those who aren't experienced with technology, and many chances to ask questions of tech-experienced nonprofits and experts.

TECHNOLOGISTS AND CONSULTANTS will find opportunities to put your expertise to social good, as well as the potential for lasting relationships (be they paid or volunteer) with leading organizations in your community.

ACTIVISTS AND COMMUNITY LEADERS will see and be given the opportunity to present on successful uses of technology for social change. Not content to simply focus on "shiny tech," we'll explore what the true potential for social change is in each case, where community organizing work can be made more effective, and where it will have to push technology forward.

Learn more about NetSquared and find your closest group at http://www.NetSquared.org
name: Tech4Good Stockholm

category.name: community/environment
description:
Do you work in the non-profit world and have questions about the new EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)? Are you wondering what GDPR means for your organisation and what needs to be done to be compliant? Would you like to meet others with similar concerns and muddle through GDPR together? Or are you passionate and knowledgeable about the topic and want to share your knowledge with others? Most importantly...do you like coffee?

Then this meet up is for you!

We are a small group of people working in the non-profit sector who are researching GDPR and want to create a meet up where, at grass roots level, we can share, discuss and put together ideas on how to prepare for this new regulation. All are welcome to the GDPR coffee meet ups! The meetings will be run entirely by the participants and every meeting will begin by collecting topic suggestions from the participants for the first few minutes. Then we will vote and start the discussions in priority order. Confirm your presence and share this event with colleagues and friends!
name: GDPR for Non-Profits

description:
I am Media and Communication Master's student at Stockholm University. Right now I am doing my final thesis which aim is to find out how people from different cultural backgrounds are interpreting news photographs of Syrian children. Previous studies have focused to study who “Western” audience interpret images of "distant other", but I am interested to find out compare if people from “distant” place see these images differently than someone, who is far away from the crisis. I am looking for volunteers, age 20-30, to participate in four focus groups:
1. Syrian women
2. Syrian men
3. Swedish/Nordic women
4. Swedish/Nordic men
The interviews will be conducted during weeks 12 and 13 in Stockholm Free snacks will be offered, and I can also help with travel expenses. Ps. Participants will remain anonymous in the final research paper: the individual’s responses or results cannot be linked to their identity.
name: Volunteers for focus group interview

category.name: community/environment
description:
The Copenhagen International Volunteer Club (CIVC) was founded in 2011 in order to bring together people of diverse backgrounds and experiences to work on issues of common interest. This group is for everyone regardless of age, nationality or experience who is interested or involved in community service and voluntary work be it in Denmark or elsewhere.

If you are interested in global issues, charity, volunteering and want to meet with others to learn more and exchange ideas , this is the group for you. No experience is necessary, just an interest in making a positive contribution. We want this meet up group to grow and become a creative and active platform for exchanging ideas and inspiration on how to make a positive change, be it on a local or global scale. And then do it.

We have several work groups that you can join: Refugee Issues, Urban Gardening & Food Systems, Animal Welfare, Medical Exchanges and Sustainable Housing in addition to our Campaigns, Logistics and Documentation group which assists the topic-focused work groups.

Our refugee work is, and has, been taking up most of our time and energy since 2013. We have been scaling back this work in recent months due to a drop in the number of refugees coming to Denmark, but there is still a lot of work to be done in this area. However, this fall the focus is shifting back to some of our other activities in sustainable housing, medical exchanges and work around issues of urban gardening and food systems. 

Sign up for one of our regularly scheduled monthly briefing sessions and find out more about how you can get involved.
name: Copenhagen International Volunteer Club
organizer.name: Andrew Madsen

description:
Thorium MSR is a new way of producing energy. When Thorium is combined with a Moltel Salt Reactor (MSR) we believe it is possible to make energy 10 times more safe than any current energy system out there. And 10 times less expensive and produce 100 times less waste than the current nuclear industry.

Moltel Salt Reactors can be used to burn spent nuclear fuel from the old generations of nuclear power plants, such that the amount of long lived waste is reduced from approx. 100.000 years to 300 years. A molten salt reactor is made from pipes and pumps and valves, thus it should be possible to get the price of energy production via MSR far below any current energy source. In this meetup group we discuss the problems and potentials of the above and what we can do to make it happen.


https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=inIVcUlQZrE
name: Thorium MSR Copenhagen

Cleanweb is a global movement that focuses on tackling big issues with software - leveraging data and ICT to do more with less resource usage.

Example of the Cleanweb: Airbnb, which helps travelers use 66 percent less energy than if they stay in a hotel. ZipCar, which replaces 15 privately owned cars for every shared car on the road. Potential for changing status-quo: HUGE

Are you excited? Are you looking to meet smart people? Expand your network, not only in Denmark but globally? Are you looking for a place to use your skills and expertise to built something that matters?

Our goal is to accelerate the development of new solutions and businesses that utilizes resources more efficiently and more sustainable - Build and share the knowledge and competencies required to build Cleanweb solutions - Establish collaborations across the traditional borders between the different communities, industries and authorities that must be involved to solve the big issues.

Let's start sharing, challenging and building new solutions - CleanwebDK

description:
One Bowl is a non-profit, community Restaurant. The community restaurant concept is a restaurant based on a gift economy, allowing people to "pay what you feel" and serving all members of the community regardless of their ability to pay. 

This is based on the values that we would like to treat everyone equal, trustworthy, with dignity without any discrimination. We also want to be socially inclusive, including everyone with their preferences, culture and celebrate diversity. We will serve vegetarian, because we can include more people with Veggies.  We are dependent on your generosity and volunteers to help us work to make our these values possible in our community. 

If your interested in being a volunteer, write to volunteer@onebowl.dk.  You don't have to be particularly skillful, we believe that if you have the passion, one can learn any skill in time.

Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/1bowl

description: Welcome to the Copenhagen Maptime chapter, Denmark's first! Maptime was an idea that came to life at the 2013 State of the Map US conference with the underlying premise to get more people involved with OpenStreetMap (OSM). Maptime Copenhagen aims to bring this idea to Denmark and get all kinds of people involved with mapping in a fun, open environment. We will be holding events at exciting locations in Greater Copenhagen using Mapillary and other tools to gather detailed information on the selected area. category.name: community/environment
description:
A group for anyone who wants to stay up to date on all events taking place at think.dk! 

PLEASE NOTE: we're also using our homepage and Facebook to promote our events.

think.dk is the Center for Acceleration of Change.

We are a co-creative community, think tank and event platform that supports the development of a sustainable society. An intersection point for Changers of all kind, making room for new ideas. We support people to share knowledge and built the future of their dreams.

We don't mind not fitting in. We are what we have to be to support the change this world needs to see. Nothing's going to change if we just sit and wait.

At think.dk, you can: 

• attend talks and movie screenings on sustainability topics

• join workshops on implementing sustainability in your everyday life 

• learn about open source programming for a more sustainable digital world 

• borrow tools or equipment from think.dk and share your own 

• find body/mind balance in our yoga classes 

• connect with like-minded people 

• use our location for your own sustainability-related event 

• help accelerate sustainable change 

Practically, we are trying to save the world.

Today, there exist numerous initiatives for a more sustainable lifestyle, but they stay hidden in niches because they lack a lobby - and people are stuck in their old habits.

This is why we host a platform for new ideas and offer events and services which further sustainability, sharing, and collaboration. 

We reconnect the dots. Question the box and restore the circle, in order to find real solutions to the problems that (will) affect us all. We experiment. Encourage discussions on new paradigms, explore new work and collaboration patterns and empower people to live more sustainably.

We want to offer serious and sustainable solutions to the problems that affect everyone every day. And we want to make a difference. We are extremely happy to say that the same goes for all of our members. What about you?

It's not about what we could do in the past, but what we can do today. We think that this is how tomorrow is made.

It is time to take the next step. 

Join us now.
name: think.dk - Center for Acceleration of Change

description:
Vårt syfte är att ha en plats där vi som jobbar (eller vill jobba) praktiskt med omställning kan resonera och byta erfarenheter. 

Tillväxttåget rusar inte längre fram men fortfarande följer det samma gamla spår. Det är svårt att hoppa av mellan stationerna men vi kan förbereda oss. 

Till att börja med kommer vi att fokusera på Tjörnarp. Enligt kommunens förslag till översiktsplan ska byn utvecklas. Översiktsplanen är utställd till den 23 mars för allmänhetens granskning. Märkligt nog jobbar man samtidigt med en besparingsplan där man föreslår att skolan ska läggas ner. 

Höörs kommun följer ett vanligt men simpelt mönster. Trots att alla kommuner vill växa så krymper de flesta och får en försämrad ekonomi. De tvingas spara där det går. Den enkla modellen är att centralisera verksamheterna till centralorten och låta byarna dö. Några tankar på att ställa om med hänsyn till den globala energi- och livsmedelssituationen har man inte. Men det har vi. 

De som vill vara med om att jobba praktiskt med en omställningsplan för Tjörnarp är välkomna att haka på. En omställningsplan för Tjörnarp skulle kunna fogas in i Höörs översiktsplan. Här har vi chansen att utveckla vår egen metod för att utarbeta lokala omställningsplaner.
name: Praktisk omställning
organizer.name: Oscar Kjellberg

description:
As many of you know the world population is growing and the future has some serious problems going on, some is just around the corner and some are in your face... The coming food crisis is one of those "problems".

(as why you probably here)

After attending a aquaponic conference, in London, I realised how young this industry is. In Europe we only have a handfull of people running an aquaponic business but at the same time a lot of people is interested in the idea of growing your own food. On my way back home, this idea struck me "Why not create a MeetUp, so the people who is interested can meet each other?!". My hope with this group is to create a place were you can bounce your Urban Farming ideas(with an special direction towards aquaponics) with other people and then learn from each others mistakes. This group will be for discussion, conversation and for networking. And if you, like me, have this "thing" in your stomach that tells you that something is wrong, then I'll see you soon.

description:
What future do you want?

The way we picture the future plays a big part in everything we do and think. Elon Musk, Sergei Brin, Mark Zuckerberg and other Silicon Valley tech entrepreneurs are currently building the future they want with self-driving cars, asteroid mining, Tesla cars, Google glass etc, inspired by thinkers like Ray Kurzweil and Peter Diamandis.

At the same time, the leaders of the Chinese government are working hard on the future they want, and send Chinese organisations to buy land in faraway countries to safeguard energy and food supplies for the 1.4 billion inhabitants at home.

There is also a growing global grass roots movements based on environmental sustainability with people who are very clear about what future they want. A clean energy future where consumerism is replaced by community and our fixation with growth on a finite planet is questioned. 

Elsewhere, at the edges of the global society, communities such as the Peer-to-peer movement, the Tibetan Buddhists and Al Qaeda are busy building the future that they want. These are communities with few people and radical ideas, but with potential to disrupt large corporations and nation states. 

This Meetup group are for those who like to explore these very different possible futures. We aim to invite people from different fields to try to make sense of trends, shifts in society and the deeper stories that lie beneath.

We will also discuss what we can do to co-create the future that we want. Because the future is not a destination. It is something we create ourselves by what we do (and don't do) in every moment.

We hope to see you soon!
name: Stockholm Futurists

description:
I have been away from Stockholm for 3 years traveling, being homeless :)

I will resume my weekly joy of feeding the homeless in Stockholm centrum area. But  now I do it Saturdays at 12 noon meeting at same place. (Sergels torget) Looking forward to meeting kind hearts.

I bring a pot of homemade soup (simple carrot, potatoe, and barley) in a pressure cooker (seals top so no spills)  in a two wheeled cart (Dramaten-vagn) and dispense in cups on location where they sit. What service!

Are they grateful? Don't expect it but we dont do it for them only but for a higher purpose. (Thats also a story)

Just in case you think doing this doesn't pay, I have a story for those who come to join me. Fact is it does pay but not from me. "What goes around comes around." You get repayed for your love in action in very tangible ways.

description:
This is a group for tech meetup organizers in Stockholm. We all face similar challenges in nurturing our communities so let's share our experiences and make Stockholm's meetup scene even better!

During the meetings, we hope to share and discuss everything from how to find great venues and speakers to  experimenting with formats, involving members, marketing, reaching outside of meetup.com, recording your meets and whatever else we might encounter in our quests to build great communities.

category.name: community/environment
description:
Welcome to the Stockholm Sustainability Meetup! This is a group for all the people interested in living a sustainable life, respecting the nature and the environment we live in. We want to promote ideas such as:

• eating locally and biologically produced food

•  recycling and repairing instead of buying new things

• sharing before possessing

• growing food while preserving biodiversity and soil fertility (for example with permaculture)

• alternative societies, such as Transition Towns

• and all the nice ideas you and us can promote!

We plan to discuss about alternative ways of thinking our way of living, creating a sense of community that our globalised, fast and often alienating society has long forgotten.

category.name: community/environment
description:
Fair Chance is about supporting children growing under challenging conditions which may hinder them from reaching their full potential and achieving their goals.

Such conditions maybe growing up with parents who are absent or disabled, for example due to drug or alcohol abuse, severe medical conditions (physical or mental), or social deprivation like unemployment, immigration, etc.

There are clear scientific evidence that these children are at significant risk to drop off school, start abusing drugs, come into criminality.

But there are also strong evidence that programs like Fair Chance can prevent this. There are components known to support children growing in alienation like programs promoting mental, social, physical development, supporting children natural curiosity and thirst for knowledge and desire to invent and create.

That is what this meetup is about. We will implement those programs IRL! 

Join us and make a difference!
name: Fair Chance

category.name: community/environment
description:
NetSquared gathers together nonprofits and activists, tech leaders and funders, and everyone who's interested in using technology for social change.

NONPROFIT STAFF will find a friendly, welcoming atmosphere for those who aren't experienced with technology, and many chances to ask questions of tech-experienced nonprofits and experts.

TECHNOLOGISTS AND CONSULTANTS will find opportunities to put your expertise to social good, as well as the potential for lasting relationships (be they paid or volunteer) with leading organizations in your community.

ACTIVISTS AND COMMUNITY LEADERS will see and be given the opportunity to present on successful uses of technology for social change. Not content to simply focus on "shiny tech," we'll explore what the true potential for social change is in each case, where community organizing work can be made more effective, and where it will have to push technology forward.

Learn more about NetSquared and find your closest group at http://www.NetSquared.org

category.name: community/environment
description:
Do you work in the non-profit world and have questions about the new EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)? Are you wondering what GDPR means for your organisation and what needs to be done to be compliant? Would you like to meet others with similar concerns and muddle through GDPR together? Or are you passionate and knowledgeable about the topic and want to share your knowledge with others? Most importantly...do you like coffee?

Then this meet up is for you!

We are a small group of people working in the non-profit sector who are researching GDPR and want to create a meet up where, at grass roots level, we can share, discuss and put together ideas on how to prepare for this new regulation. All are welcome to the GDPR coffee meet ups! The meetings will be run entirely by the participants and every meeting will begin by collecting topic suggestions from the participants for the first few minutes. Then we will vote and start the discussions in priority order. Confirm your presence and share this event with colleagues and friends!
name: GDPR for Non-Profits

description:
I am Media and Communication Master's student at Stockholm University. Right now I am doing my final thesis which aim is to find out how people from different cultural backgrounds are interpreting news photographs of Syrian children. Previous studies have focused to study who “Western” audience interpret images of "distant other", but I am interested to find out compare if people from “distant” place see these images differently than someone, who is far away from the crisis. I am looking for volunteers, age 20-30, to participate in four focus groups:
1. Syrian women
2. Syrian men
3. Swedish/Nordic women
4. Swedish/Nordic men
The interviews will be conducted during weeks 12 and 13 in Stockholm Free snacks will be offered, and I can also help with travel expenses. Ps. Participants will remain anonymous in the final research paper: the individual’s responses or results cannot be linked to their identity.

category.name: community/environment
description:
The Copenhagen International Volunteer Club (CIVC) was founded in 2011 in order to bring together people of diverse backgrounds and experiences to work on issues of common interest. This group is for everyone regardless of age, nationality or experience who is interested or involved in community service and voluntary work be it in Denmark or elsewhere.

If you are interested in global issues, charity, volunteering and want to meet with others to learn more and exchange ideas , this is the group for you. No experience is necessary, just an interest in making a positive contribution. We want this meet up group to grow and become a creative and active platform for exchanging ideas and inspiration on how to make a positive change, be it on a local or global scale. And then do it.

We have several work groups that you can join: Refugee Issues, Urban Gardening & Food Systems, Animal Welfare, Medical Exchanges and Sustainable Housing in addition to our Campaigns, Logistics and Documentation group which assists the topic-focused work groups.

Our refugee work is, and has, been taking up most of our time and energy since 2013. We have been scaling back this work in recent months due to a drop in the number of refugees coming to Denmark, but there is still a lot of work to be done in this area. However, this fall the focus is shifting back to some of our other activities in sustainable housing, medical exchanges and work around issues of urban gardening and food systems. 

Sign up for one of our regularly scheduled monthly briefing sessions and find out more about how you can get involved.
name: Copenhagen International Volunteer Club

category.name: community/environment
description:
Thorium MSR is a new way of producing energy. When Thorium is combined with a Moltel Salt Reactor (MSR) we believe it is possible to make energy 10 times more safe than any current energy system out there. And 10 times less expensive and produce 100 times less waste than the current nuclear industry.

Moltel Salt Reactors can be used to burn spent nuclear fuel from the old generations of nuclear power plants, such that the amount of long lived waste is reduced from approx. 100.000 years to 300 years. A molten salt reactor is made from pipes and pumps and valves, thus it should be possible to get the price of energy production via MSR far below any current energy source. In this meetup group we discuss the problems and potentials of the above and what we can do to make it happen.


https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=inIVcUlQZrE

description:
Cleanweb is a global movement that focuses on tackling big issues with software - leveraging data and ICT to do more with less resource usage.

Example of the Cleanweb: Airbnb, which helps travelers use 66 percent less energy than if they stay in a hotel. ZipCar, which replaces 15 privately owned cars for every shared car on the road. Potential for changing status-quo: HUGE

Are you excited? Are you looking to meet smart people? Expand your network, not only in Denmark but globally? Are you looking for a place to use your skills and expertise to built something that matters?

Our goal is to accelerate the development of new solutions and businesses that utilizes resources more efficiently and more sustainable - Build and share the knowledge and competencies required to build Cleanweb solutions - Establish collaborations across the traditional borders between the different communities, industries and authorities that must be involved to solve the big issues.

Let's start sharing, challenging and building new solutions - CleanwebDK

description:
One Bowl is a non-profit, community Restaurant. The community restaurant concept is a restaurant based on a gift economy, allowing people to "pay what you feel" and serving all members of the community regardless of their ability to pay. 

This is based on the values that we would like to treat everyone equal, trustworthy, with dignity without any discrimination. We also want to be socially inclusive, including everyone with their preferences, culture and celebrate diversity. We will serve vegetarian, because we can include more people with Veggies.  We are dependent on your generosity and volunteers to help us work to make our these values possible in our community. 

If your interested in being a volunteer, write to volunteer@onebowl.dk.  You don't have to be particularly skillful, we believe that if you have the passion, one can learn any skill in time.

Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/1bowl

PLEASE NOTE: we're also using our homepage and Facebook to promote our events.

think.dk is the Center for Acceleration of Change.

We are a co-creative community, think tank and event platform that supports the development of a sustainable society. An intersection point for Changers of all kind, making room for new ideas. We support people to share knowledge and built the future of their dreams.

We don't mind not fitting in. We are what we have to be to support the change this world needs to see. Nothing's going to change if we just sit and wait.

At think.dk, you can: 

• attend talks and movie screenings on sustainability topics

• join workshops on implementing sustainability in your everyday life 

• learn about open source programming for a more sustainable digital world 

• borrow tools or equipment from think.dk and share your own 

• find body/mind balance in our yoga classes 

• connect with like-minded people 

• use our location for your own sustainability-related event 

• help accelerate sustainable change 

Practically, we are trying to save the world.

Today, there exist numerous initiatives for a more sustainable lifestyle, but they stay hidden in niches because they lack a lobby - and people are stuck in their old habits.

This is why we host a platform for new ideas and offer events and services which further sustainability, sharing, and collaboration. 

We reconnect the dots. Question the box and restore the circle, in order to find real solutions to the problems that (will) affect us all. We experiment. Encourage discussions on new paradigms, explore new work and collaboration patterns and empower people to live more sustainably.

We want to offer serious and sustainable solutions to the problems that affect everyone every day. And we want to make a difference. We are extremely happy to say that the same goes for all of our members. What about you?

It's not about what we could do in the past, but what we can do today. We think that this is how tomorrow is made.

It is time to take the next step. 

Join us now.

description:
As many of you know the world population is growing and the future has some serious problems going on, some is just around the corner and some are in your face... The coming food crisis is one of those "problems".

(as why you probably here)

After attending a aquaponic conference, in London, I realised how young this industry is. In Europe we only have a handfull of people running an aquaponic business but at the same time a lot of people is interested in the idea of growing your own food. On my way back home, this idea struck me "Why not create a MeetUp, so the people who is interested can meet each other?!". My hope with this group is to create a place were you can bounce your Urban Farming ideas(with an special direction towards aquaponics) with other people and then learn from each others mistakes. This group will be for discussion, conversation and for networking. And if you, like me, have this "thing" in your stomach that tells you that something is wrong, then I'll see you soon.
